## Available Metrics 

The system calculates over 40 different metrics to analyze trader behavior:

```
   +---------------------------------------+
   |                                       |
   |         Trading Metrics               |
   |                                       |
   +---------------------------------------+
          |              |              |
          v              v              v
 +----------------+ +-----------+ +-------------+
 |                | |           | |             |
 | RETURNS &      | | RISK &    | | BEHAVIORAL  |
 | PROFITABILITY  | | VOLATILITY| | PATTERNS    |
 |                | |           | |             |
 +----------------+ +-----------+ +-------------+
 | â€¢ Win Rate     | | â€¢ Sharpe  | | â€¢ Momentum  |
 | â€¢ Profit Factor| | â€¢ Max     | | â€¢ Mean      |
 | â€¢ Return Ratio | |   Drawdown| |   Reversion |
 | â€¢ Cash Multiple| | â€¢ Volatil | | â€¢ Risk      |
 | â€¢ Kelly Crit.  | |   -ity    | |   Tolerance |
 +----------------+ +-----------+ +-------------+
 And many many more!
```

### Key Metric Categories:

1. **Return & Profitability**: How much you win
2. **Risk & Volatility**: How much you might lose
3. **Behavioral Patterns**: How you make decisions
4. **Time & Holding**: When you trade
5. **Market-Specific**: What you know that others don't


### Usage

1. The main.py goes through all the steps in creating the dataset.
2. It links to all scripts that run desired Compounded
3. Functions are commented out, but to recreate the dataset, uncomment them.
4. Note this can all be run for free! But API usage does have an account. I deactivatded my service account before going public, so you'll have to add your own.
5. That will output a csv.
6. Use the Full Analysis Notebook to do the analysis!
